    <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText><![CDATA[<pre>By Mr. BROUN of Georgia:H.R. 77.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:This legislation is authorized by Article I, Section 8 ofthe Constitution: ``To coin money, regulate the valuethereof, and of foreign coin, and fix the standard of weightsand measures'' and ``To provide for the punishment ofcounterfeiting the securities and current coin of the UnitedStates.'' It is also authorized by Article I, Section 8,Clause 3: ``To regulate commerce with foreign nations, andamong the several States, and with the Indian Tribes.''[Page H35]</pre>]]></constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
